msgstr "目錄"

#: ../../user/installation.rst:8
msgid "Spinning Up requires Python3, OpenAI Gym, and OpenMPI."
msgstr "Spinning Up 需要 Python3、OpenAI Gym 和 OpenMPI。"

#: ../../user/installation.rst:10
msgid ""
"Spinning Up is currently only supported on Linux and OSX. It may be "
"possible to install on Windows, though this hasn't been extensively "
"tested. [#]_"
msgstr ""
"Spinning Up 目前僅支援 Linux 和 OSX。在 Windows 上也許可以安裝，"
"但尚未經過充分測試。[#]_"

#: ../../user/installation.rst:12 ../../user/installation.rst:42
#: ../../user/installation.rst:86 ../../user/installation.rst:121
msgid "You Should Know"
msgstr "你應該知道"

#: ../../user/installation.rst:14
msgid ""
"Many examples and benchmarks in Spinning Up refer to RL environments that"
" use the `MuJoCo`_ physics engine. MuJoCo is a proprietary software that "
"requires a license, which is free to trial and free for students, but "
"otherwise is not free. As a result, installing it is optional, but "
"because of its importance to the research community---it is the de facto "
"standard for benchmarking deep RL algorithms in continuous control---it "
"is preferred."
msgstr ""
"Spinning Up 中的許多範例和基準測試 (Benchmark) 使用了基於 `MuJoCo`_ 物理引擎的"
"強化學習 (Reinforcement Learning, RL) 環境。MuJoCo 是一款需要授權的商業軟體，"
"提供免費試用且對學生免費，但其他情況下並非免費。因此，安裝它是可選的，"
"但由於它在研究社群中的重要性——它是連續控制 (Continuous Control) 領域中"
"深度強化學習 (Deep RL) 演算法基準測試的事實標準——建議安裝。"

#: ../../user/installation.rst:16
msgid ""
"Don't worry if you decide not to install MuJoCo, though. You can "
"definitely get started in RL by running RL algorithms on the `Classic "
"Control`_ and `Box2d`_ environments in Gym, which are totally free to "
"use."
msgstr ""
"不過，如果你決定不安裝 MuJoCo 也不用擔心。你完全可以使用 Gym 中的 "
"`Classic Control`_ 和 `Box2d`_ 環境來執行 RL 演算法，這些環境完全免費。"

#: ../../user/installation.rst:18
msgid ""
"It looks like at least one person has figured out `a workaround for "
"running on Windows`_. If you try another way and succeed, please let us "
"know how you did it!"
msgstr ""
"看起來至少有一個人找到了 `a workaround for running on Windows`_。"
"如果你嘗試了其他方法並成功了，請告訴我們你是怎麼做到的！"

#: ../../user/installation.rst:26
msgid "Installing Python"
msgstr "安裝 Python"

#: ../../user/installation.rst:28
msgid ""
"We recommend installing Python through Anaconda. Anaconda is a library "
"that includes Python and many useful packages for Python, as well as an "
"environment manager called conda that makes package management simple."
msgstr ""
"我們建議透過 Anaconda 安裝 Python。Anaconda 是一個包含 Python 及許多實用 "
"Python 套件的發行版，同時也包含一個名為 conda 的環境管理工具，"
"讓套件管理變得簡單。"

#: ../../user/installation.rst:30
msgid ""
"Follow `the installation instructions`_ for Anaconda here. Download and "
"install Anaconda3 (at time of writing, `Anaconda3-5.3.0`_). Then create a"
" conda Python 3.6 env for organizing packages used in Spinning Up:"
msgstr ""
"請按照 `the installation instructions`_ 來安裝 Anaconda。下載並安裝 "
"Anaconda3（撰寫本文時為 `Anaconda3-5.3.0`_）。然後建立一個 conda Python 3.6 "
"環境，用於管理 Spinning Up 所使用的套件："

#: ../../user/installation.rst:36
msgid ""
"To use Python from the environment you just created, activate the "
"environment with:"
msgstr "要使用你剛建立的環境中的 Python，請用以下指令啟動環境："

#: ../../user/installation.rst:44
msgid ""
"If you're new to python environments and package management, this stuff "
"can quickly get confusing or overwhelming, and you'll probably hit some "
"snags along the way. (Especially, you should expect problems like, \"I "
"just installed this thing, but it says it's not found when I try to use "
"it!\") You may want to read through some clean explanations about what "
"package management is, why it's a good idea, and what commands you'll "
"typically have to execute to correctly use it."
msgstr ""
"如果你是 Python 環境和套件管理的新手，這些東西很快就會讓人感到困惑或不知所措，"
"而且你在過程中可能會遇到一些障礙。（特別是，你應該預期會遇到這樣的問題：「我剛裝了"
"這個東西，但當我嘗試使用時，它卻說找不到！」）你可能會想閱讀一些清楚的說明，"
"了解什麼是套件管理、為什麼它是好主意，以及通常需要執行哪些指令來正確使用它。"

#: ../../user/installation.rst:46
msgid ""
"`FreeCodeCamp`_ has a good explanation worth reading. There's a shorter "
"description on `Towards Data Science`_ which is also helpful and "
"informative. Finally, if you're an extremely patient person, you may want"
" to read the (dry, but very informative) `documentation page from "
"Conda`_."
msgstr ""
"`FreeCodeCamp`_ 有一篇值得閱讀的好文章。`Towards Data Science`_ 上也有一篇"
"較短的介紹，同樣有幫助且資訊豐富。最後，如果你是一個非常有耐心的人，"
"你可能會想閱讀（枯燥但非常有用的） `documentation page from Conda`_。"

